Olympic hero Denise Lewis has picked up an honorary degree from the University of Wolverhampton. 

The athlete, who won heptathlon gold in the 2000 Sydney Games, received the honour 14 years after being given the freedom of the city, reported the Express and Star.

The 42-year-old, who is from Wolverhampton, said: 'It is a privilege to be back in my city and to be recognised in this way is fantastic. 

